                options: ['although', 'unless', 'therefore', 'while'],
                answer: 2,
                hint: '"Therefore" introduces a result or consequence.',
            },
            {
                id: '4-2-2',
                theme: 'Cause & Effect',
                q: '"It was dark, so she turned on the light." What relationship does "so" show?',
                options: [
                    'A contrast',
                    'A result or effect',
                    'A condition',
                    'A time sequence',
                ],
                answer: 1,
                hint: '"So" here means "as a result". Dark → she turned on the light (effect).',
            },
            {
                id: '4-2-3',
                theme: 'Cause & Effect',
                q: '"Because it rained heavily, the match was cancelled." Why was the match cancelled?',
                options: [
                    'The players were tired.',
                    'It rained heavily.',
                    'The stadium was full.',
                    'The referee arrived late.',
                ],
                answer: 1,
                hint: '"Because" introduces the cause/reason. Heavy rain caused the cancellation.',
            },
            {
                id: '4-2-4',
                theme: 'Cause & Effect',
                q: 'Which sentence BEST shows a cause-and-effect relationship?',
                options: [
                    'She likes blue and green.',
                    'He studied hard, so he passed the test.',
                    'The book was on the table.',
                    'Monday comes before Tuesday.',
                ],
                answer: 1,
                hint: '"So" signals the effect: studying hard (cause) → passing the test (effect).',
            },
            {
                id: '4-2-5',
                theme: 'Cause & Effect',
                q: '"The river flooded due to heavy rain." What caused the flood?',
                options: [
                    'The river was blocked.',
                    'The dam broke.',
                    'Heavy rain fell.',
                    'The river was very wide.',
                ],
                answer: 2,
                hint: '"Due to" introduces the cause. Heavy rain caused the river to flood.',
            },
