                hint: '"Firstly" indicates the first step in a sequence.',
            },
            {
                id: '4-3-2',
                theme: 'Sequencing',
                q: '"First I woke up. ___ I brushed my teeth." — Which word fits best?',
                options: ['Finally', 'Therefore', 'Then', 'Although'],
                answer: 2,
                hint: '"Then" shows the next step in a time sequence: first then.',
            },
            {
                id: '4-3-3',
                theme: 'Sequencing',
                q: '"After finishing lunch, she washed the dishes." — What did she do FIRST?',
                options: [
                    'She washed the dishes.',
                    'She went for a walk.',
                    'She ate lunch.',
                    'She made a phone call.',
                ],
                answer: 2,
                hint: '"After finishing lunch" tells us lunch came first, then she washed the dishes.',
            },
            {
                id: '4-3-4',
                theme: 'Sequencing',
                q: 'Which word signals the LAST step in a sequence?',
